\cite{2}. However, poor nutrition is a major problem in many communities around the world 
\cite{3}. It is one of the leading causes of death and disease globally 
\cite{4}.

There are many factors that contribute to poor nutrition. One of the main factors is lack of access to nutritious food 
\cite{5}. This is often a problem in rural communities where there are limited food options available 
\cite{6}. Another factor that contributes to poor nutrition is lack of knowledge about nutrition 
\cite{7}. This can lead to people not knowing how to eat healthy or what nutrients their bodies need 
\cite{8}. Lastly, another factor that contributes to poor nutrition is affordability of healthy food 
\cite{9}. This is often a problem in low-income communities where people cannot afford to buy nutritious food 
\cite{10}.

